WEBVTT

00:01.402 --> 00:03.502
Hello, ladies and gentlemen!
How is everyone?

00:03.571 --> 00:05.370
Adult mark:<i> The church</i>
<i> encouraged us to volunteer</i>

00:05.373 --> 00:06.438
<i> In the community.</i>

00:06.573 --> 00:08.440
<i> That's how</i>
<i> I booked my first gig.</i>

00:08.476 --> 00:10.709
You know there's a prize
for getting older?

00:10.711 --> 00:12.511
Yep, you get a trophy!

00:12.580 --> 00:14.046
Adult mark:<i> All</i>
<i> aspiring comedians</i>

00:14.181 --> 00:15.580
<i> Need stage time to grow.</i>

00:15.616 --> 00:18.383
<i> And no stage ages you faster</i>
<i> than the games room</i>

00:18.386 --> 00:19.884
<i> Of st. Martin's</i>
<i> retirement home!</i>

00:19.920 --> 00:23.722
You know, a-trophy, when you
don't use your muscles enough?

00:23.857 --> 00:25.424
Boo!

00:25.559 --> 00:27.325
Boos are for ghosts,
mr. Mullins!

00:27.361 --> 00:28.794
And you haven't passed on...

00:28.929 --> 00:29.928
Yet!

00:29.997 --> 00:31.930
Adult mark:<i> In a room</i>
<i> full of octogenarians,</i>

00:32.066 --> 00:33.532
<i> I was the one dying.</i>

00:33.601 --> 00:36.335
It's like hell's
waiting room in here.

00:36.470 --> 00:39.204
Oh, sorry, no offence.

00:39.240 --> 00:40.739
Is anyone having a birthday?

00:40.741 --> 00:42.207
Adult mark:<i> Pop came</i>
<i> along to support me--</i>

00:42.342 --> 00:43.542
<i> And get snacks.</i>

00:43.544 --> 00:45.611
Oh no, I'm not--
oh, oh, yeah.

00:45.746 --> 00:47.279
Fine, well, why not?

00:47.348 --> 00:50.081
There you are, sir.
Pudding cup?

00:50.117 --> 00:54.353
Oh!
Well, I could get used to this.

00:54.488 --> 00:56.821
What's your name, ma'am?

00:56.857 --> 00:59.691
Um, millicent.

00:59.693 --> 01:01.160
Millicent?

01:01.295 --> 01:03.295
Not millie hearn!

01:03.430 --> 01:04.863
Patrick critch!

01:04.865 --> 01:06.298
Oh!
Of course!

01:06.367 --> 01:07.832
How are you?

01:07.868 --> 01:10.168
A little bit older,
but twice as handsome.

01:10.204 --> 01:11.270
Pop: [chuckles]

01:11.405 --> 01:14.405
You're looking
your usual beautiful self.

01:14.442 --> 01:16.642
Unlike that linda foley.

01:16.644 --> 01:18.510
My god, I saw her yesterday.

01:18.546 --> 01:21.112
Millie: I heard
her son lost his license.

01:21.114 --> 01:22.847
Duis all over the place.

01:22.883 --> 01:24.382
Pop!

01:24.418 --> 01:26.251
-Huh?
-Do you mind?

01:26.386 --> 01:29.254
Anyway, ladies and gentlemen,
who likes impressions?

01:29.290 --> 01:30.388
Ha-ha.

01:30.424 --> 01:32.891
Give it up for
president ronald reagan!

01:32.927 --> 01:34.459
[applause & pop whistling]

01:34.462 --> 01:35.527
Mark: Ha-ha, thank you!

01:35.662 --> 01:38.796
I'm delighted
to be here tonight.

01:38.833 --> 01:42.334
But then again, at my age,
I'm delighted to be anywhere.

01:42.403 --> 01:44.036
[one person claps]

01:44.038 --> 01:46.872
[silence]

01:47.007 --> 01:49.408
Adult mark:<i> My first walk-out</i>
<i> needed a walker!</i>

01:49.410 --> 01:51.409
Tough crowd!

01:51.445 --> 01:53.278
Mark: Pop?
We gotta go.

01:53.347 --> 01:54.612
What's the rush?

01:54.614 --> 01:56.748
-We're gonna miss the bus!
-Good.

01:56.750 --> 02:00.351
You know, I get treated way
better here than I do at home.

02:00.387 --> 02:03.121
Oh, is that applesauce?

02:03.124 --> 02:04.356
Oh, yes.

02:04.491 --> 02:05.824
Pop: Hey, you know what?

02:05.959 --> 02:09.728
You should start hanging out
with people more your own age.

02:09.863 --> 02:11.930
Fine.

02:11.932 --> 02:13.298
Ah...

02:13.367 --> 02:14.900
[sighs calmly]

02:14.902 --> 02:17.035
Any more pudding?

02:18.439 --> 02:19.704
Ritche: How was
your show last night?

02:19.773 --> 02:21.373
Mark: Well,
the jell-o bit killed,

02:21.375 --> 02:23.442
But I lost them with
the medic alert stuff.

02:23.577 --> 02:25.276
I'm sorry I couldn't
help finish our project.

02:25.312 --> 02:26.678
It's okay.

02:26.680 --> 02:29.180
My dad wouldn't even
let me touch it.

02:29.216 --> 02:31.649
Adult mark:<i> Ritche and I</i>
<i> had been chosen to represent</i>

02:31.685 --> 02:33.652
<i> St. Bridget's at</i>
<i> the regional science fair.</i>

02:33.721 --> 02:36.588
<i> But we couldn't</i>
<i> take all the credit.</i>

02:36.723 --> 02:40.391
You know, I won
the science fair every year.

02:40.427 --> 02:41.760
Even made nationals!

02:41.895 --> 02:44.062
You mentioned it
once or twice before, dad.

02:44.098 --> 02:46.998
Come on, we can do much better
than a potato battery.

02:47.067 --> 02:48.299
"we"?

02:48.335 --> 02:50.035
Yeah, you know
what would be cool?

02:50.104 --> 02:52.737
If we had... Circuit board!

02:52.806 --> 02:54.673
[triumphant music]

02:54.742 --> 02:56.208
Adult mark:<i> Thanks</i>
<i> to ritche's dad,</i>

02:56.343 --> 02:58.076
<i> We made it to</i>
<i> regionals with...</i>

02:58.145 --> 03:00.345
<i> The whatchamacallit.</i>

03:00.480 --> 03:03.415
[radio playing from machine]

03:03.484 --> 03:06.484
<i> ♪ makin' it work,</i>
<i> takes a little longer! ♪</i>

03:06.520 --> 03:08.086
<i> ♪ makin' it work,</i>
<i> takes a little time... ♪</i>

03:08.155 --> 03:09.421
Ah!
Stop it, fox!

03:09.556 --> 03:11.189
It's a singing robot,
not a toy.

03:11.225 --> 03:13.024
Whatever it is,
it's stupid.

03:13.060 --> 03:14.426
Well, if we're the stupid ones,

03:14.495 --> 03:17.296
Then how come your project
didn't make it to regionals?

03:17.298 --> 03:21.266
At least I did
my project myself.

03:21.402 --> 03:23.502
Hey, fox!
You come to cheer us on?

03:23.637 --> 03:26.037
Oh, yes, mr. Perez.
You got this.

03:26.106 --> 03:28.240
You're definitely one of the
smartest eighth-graders here.

03:28.309 --> 03:29.507
Thanks!

03:29.543 --> 03:31.777
But remember,
if the judges ask,

03:31.779 --> 03:35.913
"lips" stands for
"light, infrared, power"--

03:35.950 --> 03:38.116
Dad, this is our project!

03:38.152 --> 03:39.584
I know!

03:39.587 --> 03:43.088
You guys,
you take it from here.

03:43.157 --> 03:45.523
Wait, I better solder that!

03:45.559 --> 03:47.558
[radio keeps playing]

03:47.595 --> 03:49.728
Mark: Come on, ritche, m'boy!

03:49.730 --> 03:52.597
Let's check out the competition.

03:52.633 --> 03:55.066
♪

03:55.102 --> 03:56.868
Tv narration: Maple syrup...

03:56.937 --> 03:58.203
Northern nectar.

03:58.338 --> 04:00.339
Look...
A single drip...

04:00.474 --> 04:01.540
And then another.

04:01.675 --> 04:04.075
We are we forced
to watch this crap?

04:04.144 --> 04:07.279
We should have freedom to watch
whatever we want on television!

04:07.348 --> 04:09.147
[loudly]
who's with me on this?

04:09.149 --> 04:10.215
What do we want?

04:10.350 --> 04:11.650
Tv freedom!

04:11.652 --> 04:13.018
When do we want it?

04:13.020 --> 04:14.285
Now, now, now!

04:14.321 --> 04:15.487
What do we want?

04:15.556 --> 04:16.988
Tv freedom!

04:17.057 --> 04:18.156
When do we want it?

04:18.292 --> 04:19.825
-Now, now, now!
-[channel switches]

04:19.827 --> 04:21.426
Tv announcer:
...Now in orillia, ontario.

04:21.428 --> 04:24.295
Oh...
Thank you, nurse.

04:24.297 --> 04:26.565
You are so assertive.

04:26.700 --> 04:27.699
You know what you want,

04:27.834 --> 04:30.468
And you're not afraid
to go out and get it.

04:30.470 --> 04:32.437
And I know what I want now.

04:32.572 --> 04:35.907
That's to have dinner
with you tomorrow.

04:35.909 --> 04:37.509
♪

04:37.644 --> 04:39.978
It's scalloped potato day.

04:40.113 --> 04:42.580
[chuckles]

04:42.616 --> 04:46.718
Look, I'm a little bit
embarrassed about this but...

04:46.720 --> 04:49.588
I was glad when
your husband died.

04:49.590 --> 04:52.958
I mean, I didn't want to
say anything at the wake.

04:52.960 --> 04:54.559
Flirt!

04:54.561 --> 04:56.027
Adult mark:<i> Things</i>
<i> were heating up</i>

04:56.096 --> 04:57.796
<i> At the retirement home.</i>

04:57.865 --> 04:59.931
Ritche: All these kids
are smarter than us.

04:59.933 --> 05:02.467
Fox: That's 'cause we go to
the dumb school, dumbass.

05:02.503 --> 05:04.069
Congrats, you were
the smartest of the dummies

05:04.138 --> 05:06.138
And now you're the dumbest
of the smarties.

05:06.273 --> 05:07.405
Ignore her, ritche.

05:07.441 --> 05:09.341
She's just not at
the regional level.

05:09.343 --> 05:13.211
♪

05:13.280 --> 05:15.180
Whoa!

05:15.315 --> 05:17.615
Who's that?

05:17.685 --> 05:20.285
Fox: Not granola...

05:20.287 --> 05:22.153
Ooh, skateboards!

05:22.222 --> 05:23.454
Cool!

05:23.490 --> 05:24.889
What's your project about?

05:25.025 --> 05:28.026
Which type of pants hold up best
when you fall off your board.

05:28.028 --> 05:29.161
Whoa.

05:29.296 --> 05:31.028
Adult mark:<i> The regional</i>
<i> science fair brought kids</i>

05:31.065 --> 05:32.764
<i> From all over</i>
<i> the province together.</i>

05:32.800 --> 05:35.100
<i> If ritche was ever</i>
<i> going to meet his match,</i>

05:35.235 --> 05:37.368
<i> It was here at nerd-palooza.</i>

05:37.404 --> 05:38.803
I'm ritche.

05:38.872 --> 05:40.905
Jacinta,
but everyone calls me jay.

05:40.974 --> 05:42.274
I'm mark.

05:42.276 --> 05:44.142
Uh, and this is fox.

05:44.144 --> 05:45.410
Jay: Fox?

05:45.446 --> 05:47.212
What's that short for?
Foxanne?

05:47.281 --> 05:49.580
Foxanne!

05:49.616 --> 05:52.184
♪ fox-anne! ♪

05:52.186 --> 05:55.987
Have fun losing, losers.

05:55.989 --> 05:57.322
She seems nice.

05:57.324 --> 05:58.623
Ritche: Yeah, she's...

05:58.759 --> 06:03.161
Adult mark:<i> Fox was</i>
<i> not about to be replaced.</i>

06:03.296 --> 06:05.330
<i> All's fair in love and war,</i>

06:05.465 --> 06:08.099
<i> If not in science fairs.</i>

06:08.102 --> 06:10.935
Wow, your board's
way better than mine.

06:11.004 --> 06:12.137
You skateboard?

06:12.272 --> 06:15.073
You guys should come
skateboarding with me downtown!

06:15.075 --> 06:16.073
Downtown?

06:16.110 --> 06:18.343
We're going down
right after the judging.

06:18.345 --> 06:21.680
We'll see you there.

06:21.815 --> 06:23.681
Ah-- wait, downtown?

06:23.751 --> 06:25.951
That's like two bus transfers!

06:28.422 --> 06:30.021
Ritche: Show time!
We gotta go!

06:30.090 --> 06:32.824
Mark: Uh, okay!

06:32.860 --> 06:34.625
When it comes to projects,

06:34.661 --> 06:39.531
St. Bridget's has it
down to a science.

06:39.666 --> 06:42.200
But we're not just all talk!

06:44.705 --> 06:46.638
Mike sr: [radio]
<i> and now, the vocm news.</i>

06:46.773 --> 06:48.473
<i> I'm mike critch.</i>

06:48.608 --> 06:50.942
<i> Two youths were apprehended</i>
<i> at the pop shoppe last night.</i>

06:51.011 --> 06:52.643
<i> The suspects were found</i>
<i> breaking bottles</i>

06:52.679 --> 06:54.779
<i> Against a dumpster</i>
<i> in the parking lot...</i>

06:54.848 --> 06:57.582
The lips should be moving,
ritche...?

06:57.584 --> 06:59.784
Ah, ritche, m'boy!

06:59.853 --> 07:01.586
Mike sr: [radio]
<i> the destructive vandals threw</i>

07:01.721 --> 07:03.054
<i> The remaining bottles</i>
<i> at police officers...</i>

07:03.090 --> 07:04.256
Mark: Um...

07:04.391 --> 07:07.826
Ha, just one second!

07:07.828 --> 07:10.061
I don't know how it works!

07:10.130 --> 07:11.496
Mark: Uh, he--

07:11.565 --> 07:13.164
Mike sr: [radio]
<i> one officer was injured</i>

07:13.200 --> 07:15.233
<i> When he slipped on a shard</i>
<i> and was rushed to...</i>

07:15.235 --> 07:16.801
What place did I get?

07:16.837 --> 07:19.070
We didn't place, dad.

07:19.139 --> 07:20.338
What?!

07:20.374 --> 07:22.474
This thing is rigged!

07:22.543 --> 07:24.141
Excuse me, miss?

07:24.178 --> 07:26.711
Excuse me, did you see
our project back there?

07:26.713 --> 07:28.012
The-- the lips?

07:28.048 --> 07:29.681
Adult mark:<i> I'd seen</i>
<i> hockey dads before,</i>

07:29.683 --> 07:31.415
<i> But never a science fair dad.</i>

07:31.452 --> 07:35.287
[upbeat music playing]

07:35.289 --> 07:36.554
Adult mark:<i> "downtownies."</i>

07:36.690 --> 07:39.090
<i> Hacky-sacking,</i>
<i> skateboarding punks.</i>

07:39.092 --> 07:40.157
Ritche: Whoa...

07:40.194 --> 07:42.694
They're desecrating
the war memorial!

07:42.696 --> 07:45.697
This is not why young men
died in the trenches!

07:45.766 --> 07:48.366
Please don't say
things like that, okay?

07:48.435 --> 07:50.101
I like jay,

07:50.137 --> 07:52.370
And I don't want
her to think we're nerds.

07:52.506 --> 07:54.306
You met at a science fair!

07:54.308 --> 07:55.640
[sighs]

07:55.709 --> 07:57.174
You want to be an actor?

07:57.211 --> 07:59.444
Maybe you can
act like you fit in.

07:59.579 --> 08:01.112
Challenge accepted.

08:01.181 --> 08:04.448
Adult mark:<i> I could</i>
<i> fake being myself.</i>

08:04.485 --> 08:08.386
[upbeat music playing]

08:08.422 --> 08:11.122
♪

08:11.158 --> 08:12.457
You made it!

08:12.526 --> 08:14.759
Ritche, mark,
this is my friend cara.

08:14.795 --> 08:15.927
Adult mark:<i> Cara!</i>

08:16.062 --> 08:18.496
<i> I'd finally met a girl</i>
<i> as nerdy as I was.</i>

08:18.631 --> 08:19.797
<i> But she wore it better.</i>

08:19.867 --> 08:21.332
Can I try your board?

08:21.368 --> 08:22.733
Sure!

08:22.769 --> 08:26.271
It's from canadian tire.

08:26.406 --> 08:28.340
Adult mark:<i> I didn't know</i>
<i> what to say to her.</i>

08:28.475 --> 08:30.742
<i> What could I have in common</i>
<i> with a downtownie girl?</i>

08:30.744 --> 08:34.145
[coughing]

08:34.147 --> 08:38.282
[romantic music]

08:38.318 --> 08:41.285
[inhaling deeply]

08:41.321 --> 08:44.289
[romantic music]

08:44.358 --> 08:46.958
♪

08:47.093 --> 08:50.795
Whoa, is-- is that
a metered dose aerosol?

08:50.831 --> 08:53.031
You know your inhalers.
You need a puff?

08:53.166 --> 08:54.832
Adult mark:<i> We hadn't</i>
<i> even kissed,</i>

08:54.868 --> 08:57.535
<i> But I could taste her</i>
<i> cotton candy smackers lip balm</i>

08:57.538 --> 08:58.637
<i> On her inhaler.</i>

08:58.772 --> 09:01.372
<i> Was this love,</i>
<i> or a lack of oxygen?</i>

09:01.408 --> 09:03.775
Thanks.
Needed that.

09:03.777 --> 09:06.143
So, what are you into,

09:06.179 --> 09:07.445
Besides breathing?

09:07.514 --> 09:08.780
Adult mark:<i> What was I into?</i>

09:08.915 --> 09:10.715
<i> I didn't know</i>
<i> what I was into yet!</i>

09:10.784 --> 09:11.850
<i> She hadn't told me!</i>

09:11.985 --> 09:14.185
Uh... Still... Wheezy.

09:14.221 --> 09:15.687
You go first.

09:15.822 --> 09:17.922
Well, I volunteer a lot.

09:17.925 --> 09:20.191
Oxfam,
youth for social justice...

09:20.327 --> 09:22.861
I organize protests
to help save the whales.

09:22.863 --> 09:25.196
And, oh, I'm a vegetarian.

09:25.265 --> 09:26.865
Oh, yeah, me too!

09:27.000 --> 09:28.199
I love vegetables.

09:28.268 --> 09:30.468
Sometimes I eat 'em
straight out of the can!

09:30.603 --> 09:33.805
[both chuckle]

09:33.807 --> 09:35.873
So, what school do you go to?

09:35.909 --> 09:37.208
Vanier academy.

09:37.277 --> 09:39.243
Adult mark:<i> No "saint"</i>
<i> in the school name?</i>

09:39.313 --> 09:40.412
<i> That meant she was a...</i>

09:40.547 --> 09:42.480
<i> Protestant!</i>

09:42.549 --> 09:44.416
<i> No wonder she was so exotic.</i>

09:44.418 --> 09:45.617
<i> No uniforms?</i>

09:45.619 --> 09:46.685
<i> No nuns?</i>

09:46.820 --> 09:48.886
<i> No guilt?</i>

09:48.922 --> 09:50.087
Officer butt: Kids!

09:50.123 --> 09:52.824
We've had some complaints
about the noise.

09:52.959 --> 09:57.462
I'm gonna have to ask you
to break it up for today.

09:57.531 --> 09:58.963
Pigs.

09:58.999 --> 10:00.898
That cop always hassles us.

10:00.934 --> 10:02.900
Adult mark:<i> This</i>
<i> I could handle.</i>

10:02.936 --> 10:05.236
I've got this.

10:05.305 --> 10:08.173
Hey, officer butt.

10:08.175 --> 10:10.642
I'm not on board
with the desecration

10:10.644 --> 10:13.044
Of a sacred monument either,

10:13.080 --> 10:18.850
But I've got a two-dollar bill
with your name on it.

10:18.852 --> 10:20.551
Lar's is still open.

10:20.621 --> 10:23.521
Why don't you go
forget about all of this

10:23.557 --> 10:26.257
And get yourself a cone?

10:26.326 --> 10:30.895
♪

10:30.897 --> 10:32.664
Officer butt: Afternoon, mary.

10:32.799 --> 10:37.001
Your son tried to
bribe a policeman.

10:37.070 --> 10:40.338
What?

10:43.577 --> 10:45.043
I can't believe it.

10:45.045 --> 10:47.612
My own son
brought home by the police.

10:47.614 --> 10:49.280
What will the neighbours say?

10:49.416 --> 10:50.881
We don't have neighbours.

10:50.917 --> 10:54.886
Mark, what were you
even doing downtown?

10:54.955 --> 10:57.589
I was trying
to impress a girl.

10:57.591 --> 10:58.756
Ah.

10:58.792 --> 11:01.492
Showin' off, more like.

11:01.528 --> 11:03.828
Well?
What's she like?

11:03.963 --> 11:05.563
Well, she's a protestant.

11:05.599 --> 11:07.165
Good god, a protestant?

11:07.234 --> 11:08.666
That could lead
to a mixed marriage.

11:08.669 --> 11:09.767
Think of the children!

11:09.836 --> 11:11.436
Well, what school
would they even go to?

11:11.571 --> 11:12.437
Give it up, will ya?

11:12.506 --> 11:14.572
's just a little date.
He's not gonna marry her!

11:14.708 --> 11:15.840
I dare say he's not!

11:15.975 --> 11:17.441
What church would
they get married in?

11:17.477 --> 11:18.576
Mary: Oh, jeez.

11:18.578 --> 11:19.643
Where would they be buried?

11:19.680 --> 11:20.879
At sea?

11:21.014 --> 11:22.646
Oh, going all
the way downtown.

11:22.683 --> 11:24.682
You must be starved.

11:24.817 --> 11:28.820
Uh, I've decided
I'm a vegetarian, so...

11:28.955 --> 11:31.322
This is all her doing, isn't it?

11:31.391 --> 11:34.726
Oh, too good for a little
meat fried up in the pan!

11:34.728 --> 11:35.826
Oh!

11:35.862 --> 11:37.928
Yeah, bet she
can't eat anything,

11:37.964 --> 11:41.532
With her fancy protestant nose
all stuck up in the air!

11:41.601 --> 11:43.334
I--
mom!

11:43.370 --> 11:47.238
Jesus christ,
there's no meat in gravy!

11:47.240 --> 11:49.474
[sighs]

11:51.478 --> 11:53.811
Pop: You know, they have
these wonderful chairs;

11:53.880 --> 11:57.015
They were called, uh,
lah-zee-boys.

11:57.017 --> 12:00.585
It was like sitting on
a cloud with cup holders.

12:02.589 --> 12:04.355
What do you think, pop?

12:04.357 --> 12:08.626
Everyone knows the best way to
save a whale is in the freezer.

12:08.762 --> 12:10.028
But they're endangered!

12:10.163 --> 12:12.863
You mean danger-ous.

12:12.899 --> 12:15.233
My father was killed by a whale.

12:15.368 --> 12:16.501
He was a whaler!

12:16.503 --> 12:20.037
Yeah, sharks of the sea,
that's what whales are.

12:20.107 --> 12:24.509
Anyway, since when have you
gone so brigitte bardot on us?

12:27.481 --> 12:29.247
Cara likes whales.

12:30.517 --> 12:33.518
You know, pretending to be
someone you're not for a girl,

12:33.520 --> 12:34.985
I mean...

12:35.021 --> 12:36.988
It can only lead to heartbreak.

12:37.057 --> 12:39.758
But aren't you pretending
to live at the home?

12:39.893 --> 12:41.926
Home is where the heart is,

12:42.061 --> 12:45.162
And my heart is at the home.

12:45.198 --> 12:48.132
Well, I won't rat you out
to the orderlies

12:48.201 --> 12:50.468
If you donate to our protest.

12:50.470 --> 12:52.137
Hippie!

12:54.607 --> 12:57.875
That meal was almost
as good as the company.

12:57.911 --> 13:00.311
You are such a charmer.

13:00.447 --> 13:01.145
[chuckles]

13:01.214 --> 13:03.815
Why don't we just take a stroll?

13:03.817 --> 13:06.017
See the sunset,
just the two of us.

13:06.019 --> 13:07.886
That's a lovely idea.

13:08.021 --> 13:09.821
I can show you my roses.

13:09.956 --> 13:11.422
And the creek behind the house

13:11.458 --> 13:14.292
Is just full of trout
at this time of year.

13:14.427 --> 13:15.426
Creek?

13:15.495 --> 13:16.561
I didn't see a creek.

13:16.630 --> 13:18.163
I saw a road.

13:18.298 --> 13:19.831
Oh...

13:19.833 --> 13:21.599
But...

13:23.036 --> 13:25.837
[on radio]<i> ♪ I'd like to</i>
<i> get to know you... ♪</i>

13:25.906 --> 13:28.506
This isn't my house.

13:28.575 --> 13:30.708
Millie?

13:30.844 --> 13:32.309
I have to get back before dark.

13:32.345 --> 13:35.613
My husband...
My husband will worry.

13:37.818 --> 13:41.419
Have you seen my husband, sir?

13:41.488 --> 13:42.887
No.

13:42.889 --> 13:45.657
Not for a while.
Ah...

13:45.659 --> 13:48.359
I'm afraid, he...

13:48.494 --> 13:50.128
Ah.

13:50.263 --> 13:54.332
Millie, thank you
so much for dinner.

13:55.935 --> 13:58.202
Nurse...

13:58.205 --> 14:00.672
Nurse, I think millie's tired.

14:00.807 --> 14:02.773
Take good care of her.

14:02.843 --> 14:05.443
Sir?
The doors are locked now.

14:05.512 --> 14:07.478
Locked, well,
I don't live here.

14:07.547 --> 14:09.881
Sounds like you're
a little tired, too.

14:10.016 --> 14:13.217
Um, millie, tell her who I am!

14:13.286 --> 14:15.686
I've never seen you
before in my life.

14:15.722 --> 14:17.488
What?
Hey, excuse me.

14:17.524 --> 14:18.489
Just relax now, sir.

14:18.491 --> 14:19.690
These men will get you settled.

14:19.726 --> 14:21.893
[on radio]<i> mike critch,</i>
<i> here with the vocm update!</i>

14:22.028 --> 14:23.394
Pop: Hey, whoa, whoa,
wait a minute!

14:23.529 --> 14:25.029
That's my son,
on the radio!

14:25.164 --> 14:27.064
I live with the man
on the radio!

14:27.100 --> 14:28.633
I'm sure you do.

14:28.635 --> 14:30.168
Let me go!

14:30.303 --> 14:32.036
You're gonna hear
from my lawyer!

14:32.105 --> 14:34.038
Come on, what are you doing!

14:34.074 --> 14:35.806
Protestors: Save the whales!

14:35.842 --> 14:37.709
Save the whales!

14:37.844 --> 14:39.510
Save the whales...!

14:39.579 --> 14:40.979
Save the whales!

14:41.114 --> 14:42.347
Save the whales...!

14:42.482 --> 14:43.982
Adult mark:<i> Protestants</i>
<i> sure loved to protest.</i>

14:44.117 --> 14:46.117
<i> I guess that's where</i>
<i> the name comes from.</i>

14:46.119 --> 14:47.518
Everyone's ignoring us.

14:47.554 --> 14:50.021
Don't they get
how important this is?

14:50.023 --> 14:51.956
Hang on.

14:51.992 --> 14:53.491
Listen up, everybody!

14:53.560 --> 14:56.393
I think our chant
could use some work.

14:56.429 --> 14:58.663
How about...

14:58.732 --> 15:00.932
One, two, three, four,

15:01.067 --> 15:03.167
Save our whales and ocean floor!

15:03.169 --> 15:05.069
All: One, two, three, four,

15:05.138 --> 15:08.405
Save our whales and ocean floor!

15:08.441 --> 15:10.541
I love how passionate you are.

15:10.543 --> 15:13.610
Adult mark:<i> This was the start</i>
<i> of a personal reformation.</i>

15:13.647 --> 15:16.748
What are you losers
bawling about?

15:16.883 --> 15:18.750
Who you calling
a loser, foxanne?

15:18.885 --> 15:21.819
Them, ja-cinta.

15:21.888 --> 15:23.421
I don't think mark's a loser.

15:23.556 --> 15:25.556
Fox: Then you should
get your glasses checked.

15:25.558 --> 15:28.859
Why don't you go some place
where somebody wants you?

15:28.929 --> 15:30.060
Fox...

15:30.062 --> 15:31.028
Whatever.

15:31.164 --> 15:32.830
Nobody cares about this stuff.

15:32.866 --> 15:34.232
Tree-huggin' pinkos.

15:34.367 --> 15:36.034
What did you call me?

15:36.036 --> 15:37.168
Back off!

15:37.237 --> 15:39.103
Do you know who my brothers are?

15:39.105 --> 15:40.505
No.

15:40.507 --> 15:43.607
Mark: Maybe you should
just go, fox.

15:43.643 --> 15:45.743
[chanting continues]

15:45.779 --> 15:47.312
They're faking, you know?

15:47.447 --> 15:50.948
They don't care about the whales
or the ocean or any of you.

15:50.951 --> 15:53.250
And... They're catholic!

15:53.320 --> 15:57.288
[chanting continues]

15:57.357 --> 15:58.723
Hm!

15:58.725 --> 16:01.392
♪

16:01.527 --> 16:04.128
I-I...

16:10.537 --> 16:13.871
♪

16:13.873 --> 16:16.473
Mr. Mullins: Family finally
had enough of you, eh?

16:16.509 --> 16:19.343
My son did the same thing to me.

16:19.346 --> 16:23.681
He finally gets married
and then he ships me off here.

16:23.750 --> 16:26.083
Friggin' ingrate.

16:26.152 --> 16:27.217
Ah.

16:27.253 --> 16:29.354
That's a bit selfish, huh?

16:29.489 --> 16:31.756
Well, you're probably
better off here.

16:31.825 --> 16:33.157
I mean, it's a nice place.

16:33.193 --> 16:34.959
Nice people.

16:35.094 --> 16:38.295
No, I'm just here
temporarily, yeah.

16:38.365 --> 16:39.764
I live with my son.

16:39.833 --> 16:42.466
He'd gonna come pick me up.

16:42.502 --> 16:46.437
Sounds like
you've got a good one.

16:46.473 --> 16:47.705
Yeah.

16:47.774 --> 16:49.774
Hm, I do.

16:53.179 --> 16:54.679
Millie?
Excuse me.

16:54.814 --> 16:55.980
Millie!

16:56.115 --> 16:57.115
Hey, millie!
Hey--

16:57.117 --> 16:58.682
I can't find my husband!

16:58.752 --> 17:00.151
Have you seen him?

17:00.286 --> 17:01.652
Millie, listen.
It's...

17:01.654 --> 17:03.854
-He promised me--
-it's alright.

17:03.890 --> 17:05.923
Millie...
Millie.

17:06.059 --> 17:08.993
You think he's alright?

17:08.995 --> 17:10.795
Well, there...

17:10.864 --> 17:13.264
There's a big storm moving in.

17:13.333 --> 17:15.066
They've closed down
all the roads.

17:15.201 --> 17:17.835
I mean, you wouldn't want him
driving in those conditions,

17:17.904 --> 17:19.036
Now, would you?

17:19.171 --> 17:20.404
No.

17:20.440 --> 17:23.540
So he called and he said
he's gonna pick you up

17:23.576 --> 17:25.810
First thing in the morning.

17:25.812 --> 17:27.544
Isn't that nice?

17:27.546 --> 17:30.014
Now, let's get you back
to your room, alright?

17:30.083 --> 17:31.215
Oh...

17:31.350 --> 17:33.784
Well, that makes sense.

17:33.853 --> 17:35.219
Pop, for god's sake.

17:35.288 --> 17:37.288
Oh, about bloody time!

17:37.290 --> 17:39.223
Now, listen, millie.

17:39.225 --> 17:42.159
This very nice lady
is going to take you back.

17:42.228 --> 17:45.163
And then,
if she doesn't want a lawsuit,

17:45.165 --> 17:48.299
She's gonna go to the kitchen
and get a case of that pudding,

17:48.368 --> 17:51.335
And put it in my son's car.

17:54.741 --> 17:56.774
Alright, pop, let's go.
Mary's worried sick.

17:56.843 --> 17:58.676
Wait.

17:58.811 --> 18:02.914
You know, I know I may
seem ungrateful at times...

18:02.916 --> 18:04.782
[voice cracking]

18:07.253 --> 18:10.254
[emotional]
you're a good boy.

18:10.290 --> 18:12.122
Good god!

18:12.158 --> 18:14.392
What kind of pills
you have him on?

18:20.867 --> 18:24.835
Technically, I never said
we were protestants.

18:24.838 --> 18:27.471
I don't care if
you're catholic, mark.

18:27.540 --> 18:29.907
But I do care if you're honest.

18:35.081 --> 18:37.148
Can we start again?

18:37.150 --> 18:38.216
I'm mark.

18:38.351 --> 18:40.817
I like dean martin
and vienna sausages.

18:40.854 --> 18:42.553
I'm not a vegetarian.

18:42.688 --> 18:46.624
In fact, the only vegetable
I ever eat is the noble potato.

18:49.062 --> 18:51.161
Still just cara.

18:51.197 --> 18:54.098
♪

18:54.167 --> 18:57.501
♪

18:57.537 --> 19:02.773
♪

19:02.809 --> 19:04.342
Pop...?

19:07.246 --> 19:11.715
Does making new friends mean
you have to lose your old ones?

19:11.784 --> 19:13.217
No.

19:13.219 --> 19:15.920
You can have as many friends
as you want.

19:15.989 --> 19:18.122
The only thing that matters is

19:18.191 --> 19:20.925
How many friends
you can count on.

19:21.060 --> 19:25.596
Those friends are like
a bottle of gravy browning.

19:25.632 --> 19:26.931
What?

19:27.000 --> 19:29.767
You'll have 'em till you die.

19:30.837 --> 19:32.537
Hm.

19:32.672 --> 19:36.807
[soft, sentimental music]

19:36.876 --> 19:38.942
♪

19:38.978 --> 19:42.613
♪

19:42.682 --> 19:45.215
Thank god.

19:45.251 --> 19:49.220
Adult mark:<i> In life, there's</i>
<i> family and there's friends.</i>

19:49.355 --> 19:52.823
♪

19:52.825 --> 19:55.092
♪

19:55.161 --> 19:58.028
♪

19:58.064 --> 20:00.831
Oh, hey!
How's it goin'?

20:00.967 --> 20:03.901
Adult mark:<i> And then there's</i>
<i> friends who become family.</i>

20:04.036 --> 20:05.769
Hey.

20:05.838 --> 20:07.571
About yesterday...

20:07.640 --> 20:09.440
It's fine if you
have new friends.

20:09.509 --> 20:11.575
It's just...

20:11.611 --> 20:15.779
I feel like we don't really
hang out that much anymore.

20:15.848 --> 20:16.847
Yeah.

20:16.916 --> 20:18.983
I know what you mean.

20:19.052 --> 20:20.918
♪

20:20.920 --> 20:22.853
How 'bout we go to
mary brown's for lunch?

20:22.855 --> 20:24.121
My treat.

20:24.123 --> 20:25.422
I thought you were vegetarian.

20:25.557 --> 20:27.591
I'll just have
the taters and the gravy.

20:27.660 --> 20:30.661
There's no meat in gravy, sure.

20:30.663 --> 20:33.731
♪

20:33.800 --> 20:36.067
♪

20:36.069 --> 20:38.602
♪

20:38.638 --> 20:40.671
Adult mark:<i> Sometimes,</i>
<i> when you meet a new friend,</i>

20:40.806 --> 20:44.207
<i> You can tell right away</i>
<i>that you'll be friends forever</i> .

20:44.244 --> 20:45.809
Jay: Give it a try.

20:45.878 --> 20:47.812
<i> ♪</i>

20:47.814 --> 20:50.347
Adult mark:<i> And when</i>
<i> forever comes,</i>

20:50.383 --> 20:55.186
<i> You'll be glad</i>
<i> that they're there.</i>

20:55.188 --> 20:57.187
You mind if I sit?

20:57.223 --> 21:02.026
Oh, not at all.

21:02.028 --> 21:04.028
Ah...

21:04.097 --> 21:06.063
I'm millicent.

21:06.198 --> 21:07.264
Oh...

21:07.300 --> 21:08.966
Patrick.

21:09.035 --> 21:11.302
Nice to meet you.

21:11.371 --> 21:14.905
♪

21:14.941 --> 21:18.909
♪

21:18.911 --> 21:22.847
♪

21:22.982 --> 21:27.184
♪

21:27.320 --> 21:31.655
♪

21:31.658 --> 21:35.793
♪

21:35.928 --> 21:40.164
♪

21:40.166 --> 21:44.268
♪

21:44.403 --> 21:48.739
♪

